
1. Using Insert Function, give examples of any function available in the different dropdowns present in the function library. For example AutoSum, Recently Used, Text, Date & Time, etc.
Examples of Functions in Different Dropdowns:
AutoSum:

Usage: Adds up numbers in a range.
Location: Formulas tab > AutoSum dropdown.
Recently Used:

Usage: Displays recently used functions.
Location: Formulas tab > Insert Function > Recently Used.
Text:

Example Function: LEFT(text, num_chars)
Usage: Returns a specified number of characters from the start of a text string.
Location: Formulas tab > Insert Function > Text.
Date & Time:

Example Function: TODAY()
Usage: Returns the current date.
Location: Formulas tab > Insert Function > Date & Time.
2. What are the different ways you can select columns and rows?
Selecting Columns:

Click and Drag:

Click on the column header and drag across adjacent columns.
Ctrl + Spacebar:

Press Ctrl + Spacebar to select the entire column of the active cell.
Ctrl + Click:

Hold Ctrl and click on multiple column headers to select non-adjacent columns.
Selecting Rows:

Click and Drag:

Click on the row header and drag across adjacent rows.
Shift + Spacebar:

Press Shift + Spacebar to select the entire row of the active cell.
Shift + Click:

Hold Shift and click on multiple row headers to select non-adjacent rows.
3. What is AutoFit and why do we use it?
AutoFit:

Usage: AutoFit adjusts the width of a column or the height of a row to fit the content within it.

How to AutoFit:

Column Width: Double-click the right boundary of the column header.
Row Height: Double-click the bottom boundary of the row header.
Why Use It:

Ensures that all content in a cell is visible.
Improves the overall appearance of the spreadsheet.
4. How can you insert new rows and columns into the existing table?
Inserting Rows:

Select Row:

Click on the row below where you want to insert new rows.
Right-Click and Insert:

Right-click and choose "Insert" from the context menu.
Inserting Columns:

Select Column:

Click on the column to the right of where you want to insert new columns.
Right-Click and Insert:

Right-click and choose "Insert" from the context menu.
5. How do you hide and unhide columns in excel?
Hide Columns:

Select Columns:

Select the columns you want to hide.
Right-Click and Hide:

Right-click on the selected columns and choose "Hide."
Unhide Columns:

Select Adjacent Columns:

Select the columns on either side of the hidden columns.
Right-Click and Unhide:

Right-click and choose "Unhide" from the context menu.
6. Create an appropriate table within the worksheet and use different functions available in the AutoSum command.
Steps to Create Table and Use AutoSum:

Enter Data:

Enter data in a range, ensuring it's organized in rows and columns.
Select Data:

Highlight the range of data you want to sum.
AutoSum:

Go to the "Formulas" tab.
Click on "AutoSum" in the "Editing" group.
Review Result:

The sum of the selected range will be automatically calculated and displayed in the last row or column of the selected range.
Experiment with other functions available in the AutoSum dropdown, such as Average, Count, Max, Min, etc., based on your data and analysis requirements.
